+### Patch Artifact Rules (Canonical)
+
+> **Key principle**: Since we do NOT commit during runs, `HEAD` often does not advance. Therefore, the canonical cumulative patch must reflect **develop ΓåÆ working tree** (including staged and unstaged changes), NOT `develop...HEAD`.
 
 - **Patch artifact must be regenerated at end of every run** (after all changes and after `pnpm gates`)
 - **Use PowerShell UTF-8 method** ΓÇö do NOT use `>` (can produce UTF-16)
 - **No paraphrased sizes** (e.g., "~260KB" or "approximately 260 KB" is forbidden)
-- **Only one patch size per day** ΓÇö overwrite prior value when regenerating
+- **Only one patch size per day** ΓÇö only one recorded size entry for `artifacts/day-<N>.patch` in merge-notes.md (overwrite old entries when regenerating)
 - **If code changes after patch generation, regenerate** before stopping
 - **Merge-notes must not contain multiple patch sizes for the same day**
 - **Always overwrite** prior patch size when regenerating (one source of truth)
+- **Always exclude `artifacts/` folder** from the patch content
+
+#### Preflight (required at START of every run):
+
+Run `git status --porcelain` at the start and record the output in merge-notes. This determines the incremental patch filename.
+
+#### Two patches required at the end of each prompt run:
+
+1. **Cumulative day patch (required):** `artifacts/day-<N>.patch` ΓÇö all changes from develop baseline to current working tree
+2. **Incremental patch (conditional filename):**
+   - If preflight `git status --porcelain` was **empty**: generate `artifacts/day-<N>-this-run.patch`
+   - If preflight `git status --porcelain` was **NOT empty**: generate `artifacts/day-<N>-working-tree.patch` instead and document why in merge-notes
+
+#### PowerShell UTF-8 commands (required):
 
-**PowerShell UTF-8 command (required):**
+**Cumulative day patch:**
 
 ```powershell
+git add -N .
 New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force artifacts | Out-Null
-git diff develop...HEAD | Out-File -FilePath artifacts/day-<N>.patch -Encoding utf8
+git diff --binary develop -- . ":(exclude)artifacts" | Out-File -FilePath artifacts/day-<N>.patch -Encoding utf8
 Get-Item artifacts/day-<N>.patch | Format-List Name,Length,LastWriteTime
 ```
 
+**Incremental patch (filename depends on preflight `git status --porcelain`):**
+
+```powershell
+git add -N .
+# If preflight was EMPTY at start of run ΓåÆ day-<N>-this-run.patch
+# If preflight was NOT empty at start ΓåÆ day-<N>-working-tree.patch
+$patchName = "day-<N>-this-run.patch"  # or "day-<N>-working-tree.patch"
+git diff --binary HEAD -- . ":(exclude)artifacts" | Out-File -FilePath artifacts/$patchName -Encoding utf8
+Get-Item artifacts/$patchName | Format-List Name,Length,LastWriteTime
+```
+
+#### Bash equivalent (short):
+
+**Cumulative day patch:**
+
+```bash
+git add -N .
+mkdir -p artifacts
+git diff --binary develop -- . ':(exclude)artifacts' > artifacts/day-<N>.patch
+ls -lh artifacts/day-<N>.patch
+```
+
+**Incremental patch (filename depends on preflight):**
+
+If working tree was clean at start, write `day-<N>-this-run.patch`. If not clean, write `day-<N>-working-tree.patch` instead.
+
+```bash
+# Clean start:
+git add -N .
+git diff --binary HEAD -- . ':(exclude)artifacts' > artifacts/day-<N>-this-run.patch
+ls -lh artifacts/day-<N>-this-run.patch
+
+# Not clean start:
+git add -N .
+git diff --binary HEAD -- . ':(exclude)artifacts' > artifacts/day-<N>-working-tree.patch
+ls -lh artifacts/day-<N>-working-tree.patch
+```
+
 ### Patch Artifact Checklist
 
 Before ending every Cursor run, verify:
 
 - [ ] Patch regenerated at end (overwritten)
 - [ ] Patch written as UTF-8 (PowerShell `Out-File -Encoding utf8`)
+- [ ] Patch uses develop baseline (NOT `develop...HEAD`)
+- [ ] Patch excludes `artifacts/` folder
 - [ ] `Get-Item ... | Format-List` output pasted into merge-notes
 - [ ] No diffs pasted into merge-notes
 
